
[1]alkermes

   ALKERM'ES, n.

   In pharmacy, a compound cordial, in the form of a confection, derived
   from the kermes berries. Its other ingredients are said to be
   pippin-cider, rose water, sugar, ambergris, musk, cinnamon, aloes-wood,
   pearls, and leaf-gold.
